==Box office performance==
The film had a 50 days run in 101 centres,<ref>[http://www.idlebrain.com/trade/records/kushi50days.html Kushi 50 days centres]</ref> 100 days run in 79 centres<ref>[http://www.idlebrain.com/trade/records/kushi100days.html Kushi 100 days centres]</ref> and a 175-day run in five centres.<ref>http://www.cinegoer.com/pawankalyan175.htm</ref>
It also set a record for highest grossing film in the [[Nizam State]] of [[Andhra Pradesh]] where it earned {{INR}}200&nbsp;million in only 100 days.<ref>{{cite web |url= http://sify.com/movies/telugu/fullstory.php?id=14641958&cid=14625527 |title= Andhra Box Office: Jalsa creates a record |date= 10 April 2008 |work= Sify |accessdate=7 November 2009 }}</ref>
Khushi grossed {{INRConvert|20|c}} in 100 Days all over the world.It collected {{INRConvert|23|c}} in 150 Days worldwide. The total collections are 22-23 crores. This was the 2nd biggest telugu hit film in 2001 after Narasimha naidu. <ref>http://www.sbdbforums.com/post/kushi-no-2-blockbuster-in-2001-5312576, http://www.idlebrain.com/trade/records/kushitotal.html, Sitara Magazine </ref>

===Records===
Kushi grossed {{INR}} 60&nbsp;lakhs in many theatres across the state.
Sandhya 70mm dts A/C officials spoke that Kushi collected {{INRConvert|1.3|c}} from their theater in 160 Days.<ref>http://dailyupdatesof.tripod.com/megabrothers/id5.html</ref>
Kushi 2001 was released in 200 theaters worldwide later on after 2 years it was Re-released in 160 theaters.



===Pre-release business===
Gemini tv bought the satellite rights of the film for {{INR}} 1.5 crores later after span of a decade Maatv group renewed this film for the same price this film was a blockbuter on television and got decent TRP's.
Music rights and home media rights were sold for {{INRConvert|40|l}} It did great business in each of its segments.

==Soundtrack==
[[Manisharma]] composed the soundtrack of the film.The audio was released in [[Hyderabad, India|Hyderabad]] and became an instant hit.The audio was released in CD's for the time in Telugu along with cassettes by Aditya Music.A classic song called "Aaduvari Maatalaku" penned by [[Pingali]] from the movie Missama was remixed by Manisharma.It was sung by Murali.All the songs became chart-busters especially Ammaye Sannaga song penned by [[Chandrabose (lyricist)|Chandra Bose]] and sung by [[Udit Narayan]] and [[Kavita Krishnamurthy]].Other lyricists are [[A.M. Ratnam]], [[Abbas Tyrewala]], [[Chandrabose (lyricist)|Chandra Bose]], [[Pingali]] and [[Suddala Ashok Teja]].

